'''Multiple-valued current mode logic''' (MVCML) or current mode multiple-valued logic (CM-MVL) is a method of representing electronic logic levels in [[analog circuit|analog]] [[CMOS]] [[Electrical network|circuit]]s.  In MVCML, logic levels are represented by multiples of a base [[Current (electricity)|current]], I<sub>base</sub>, set to a certain value, x.  Thus, level 0 is associated with the value of [[Null character|null]], level 1 is associated with I<sub>base</sub> = x, level 2 is represented by I<sub>base</sub> = 2x, and so on.

