'''Velke Kostolany transmitter''' is the main transmission facility of [[Television in Slovakia|Slovakian broadcasting company]], situated north of [[Velke Kostolany]] near [[Nitra]] and also known as ''Nitra transmitter''. It was inaugurated in 1949 and is used for [[mediumwave]] and [[shortwave]] broadcasting. For mediumwave broadcasting a 140 metres tall [[guyed mast]] is used. Until 2003 it transmitted in the mediumwave band on 1098&nbsp;kHz with [[Omnidirectional antenna|omnidirectional]] radiation, today the radiated power may be only fifty kilowatts.

